HEADWORD: Bowenite
<hw>Bow"en*ite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From G.T.
<ets>Bowen</ets>, who analyzed it in 1822.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A hard, compact variety of serpentine found in Rhode Island. It is
of a light green color and resembles jade.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

